    "comment": "Rationale: Note: Netrin-G2; NTNG2 is a postsynaptic protein.\n\nFig.4: \"NGL-2 expression in heterologous cells induces functional presynaptic differentiation in contacting neurites.\"\nFig.5: \"Beads bearing the ectodomain of NGL-2 induce functional excitatory presynaptic differentiation in contacting neurites\". Experimental description: Methods\nImmunoelectron microscopy.\nFor quantitative electron microscopy, we used two immunoreacted sections from each of two rats labeled with secondary antibody to rabbit Fab fragments coupled to 10 nm gold particles (British BioCell).\n\nCoculture assay.\nCoculture assays were performed essentially as described (17,18).\n(ref. 17) Cell Culture.\nHippocampal neuron cultures were prepared from E18 rat embryos.\n\nDNA constructs.\nFull-length mouse NGL-2 (DQ177325, aa 1-652; from a brain cDNA library; Clontech) and NGL-2 ΔC (1-649) were subcloned into pEGFP-N1.",
